fulness, this publication will be of interest to both experienced and inexperienced researchers studying Grice's philosophy, irony, deception and/or humour.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Mrz 2018) 4aDeception. 4aGrice. 4aHumor. 4aIrony. 4aPragmatics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018 Englishz978311060407808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018z9783110603170oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz978-1-5015-0789-20 cprintz978150151642940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501507922423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501507922.jpg  a978-3-11-060407-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DSPb2018